caption: This lovely garden square is literally hidden in plain sight, the surrounding streets with tourists, cruising around, looking for somewhere to have lunch, however, just through the gates there was plenty of seating, the gardens were bursting with spring colour, only a few locals were enjoying the lunch, in the peace of this tranquil garden.

Small, very green square with fragments of destroyed buildings from the adjacent Saint Germain des Pr√©s church, a visit of which is essential. Bears the name of the deputy of the 3rd Republic Laurent Prache (1856-1919) Bust of Dora Maar by Pablo Picasso dedicated to Guillaume Apolinaire.

On the square there is a monument to Pablo Picasso ‚ÄúMonument to Apollinaire‚Äù (1959) or ‚ÄúHead of a Woman‚Äù (Dora Maar). This statue was stolen in 1999 and found in a ditch in the municipality of Oni by a road worker. The municipality of Oni, unaware of the origin of the sculpture, displays it in the hall of the town hall. In 2001, one of the visitors to the town hall recognizes the bust as a work by Picasso, after which the sculpture returns to its old place

The Laurent Prache square. It is located next to Place Juliette Greco. A very original idea for a great artist who spent her entire life in the neighborhood.
